Modal dialog for user consent before model download.

## Dialog Design
```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│  Semantic Search                                            │
├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│                                                             │
│  Semantic search requires a 23MB model download from        │
│  HuggingFace (sentence-transformers/all-MiniLM-L6-v2).      │
│                                                             │
│  After download, the model runs locally.                    │
│  Your search data never leaves your machine.                │
│                                                             │
│  [D] Download   [H] Hash mode (approximate)   [Esc] Cancel  │
│                                                             │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

## Text Accuracy Fix
OLD (misleading): "No data is sent to external services"
NEW (accurate): "Your search data never leaves your machine"

We DO contact HuggingFace to download - being clear about this builds trust.

## Key Handling
- D → Start download, close prompt, show progress in status bar
- H → Enable hash mode (SEM*), close prompt, switch to SEM
- Esc → Cancel, close prompt, stay on current mode

## Cancel During Download
While download is in progress:
- Status bar shows: "⬇️ 45% (Esc to cancel)"
- Esc cancels download, reverts to NotInstalled state
- Partial files are cleaned up
- User can retry later

## UX Considerations
- Prompt ONLY appears when user actively switches to SEM/HYB
- Never auto-appears on startup
- Remember hash choice (don't re-prompt if user chose H)
- Dismissable without action
- Cancel download is always available

